text: Mary Seymour (30 August 1548 - 1550?) Was the only child of Catherine Parr and her fourth husband, Thomas Seymour, 1st Baron Seymour of Sudeley. Complications from Mary's birth had took the life of Catherine on 5 September 1548 when Mary was just 6 days old. Mary had vanished from records in 1550, coming to the conclusion that she possibly died. However some theory's think she lived to adulthood.
